text: Acanthopagrus morrisoni, commonly known as the western yellowfin seabream, also known as the yellow sea bream or datina, is a porgy of the family Sparidae. It was recognised as a distinct species separate from latus in 2013. ==References== ==External links== * Fishes of Australia : Acanthopagrus morrisoni western yellowfin seabream Category:Marine fish of Northern Australia western yellowfin seabream
title: Acanthopagrus morrisoni
